Bungoma governor hopeful Alfred Khang&rsquo;ati (pictured) yesterday asked Ford Kenya leader Moses Wetang&rsquo;ula to stick to his presidential bid and not run for governor.He said Wetang&rsquo;ula should prepare to lose if he runs for governor. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m certain that I&rsquo;m going to win this seat. We welcome our senator into the race.This will complicate matters for other aspirants but I will still pass through them because I have got support across the board,&rdquo; Khang&rsquo;ati said. He spoke to reporters in Bungoma town.